In terms of treatment, anticoagulant medications are widely used for managing venous thromboembolism. These medications help prevent the growth of blood clots and reduce the risk of complications. Thrombolytic therapy is another treatment option that helps dissolve blood clots quickly, especially in severe cases of venous thromboembolism. Surgical interventions such as thrombectomy or placement of a vena cava filter may be required in certain cases to address the blood clots effectively. End-users of venous thromboembolism products and services, including hospitals, clinics, diagnostic centers, and ambulatory surgical centers, play a crucial role in the management and treatment of patients with venous thromboembolism.

